---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Terms of Use | pedestrianaccidentcalc.com';
const description = 'Terms of use for pedestrianaccidentcalc.com — informational use only, no professional relationship, and limitation of liability.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> January 1, 2026</p>

  <h2>Informational Use Only</h2>
  <p>All content on pedestrianaccidentcalc.com — including the calculator, guides, methodology, and FAQ — is provided for informational and educational purposes only. Nothing on this site constitutes legal advice or creates a professional relationship. Calculator results are estimates based on documented multiplier frameworks and fault rules; they do not predict outcomes for any specific case.</p>
  <p>Actual settlement outcomes depend on specific facts that the calculator cannot know: the at-fault driver's policy limits, the specific comparative fault percentage a jury or adjuster would assign, medical documentation quality, local verdict patterns, and negotiating skill. The ranges are educational tools, not legal predictions.</p>

  <h2>No Professional Relationship</h2>
  <p>Use of this site does not create an attorney-client relationship or any other professional relationship. Contact with the editorial team does not create a professional relationship or obligation to provide professional services.</p>

  <h2>Consult Qualified Professionals</h2>
  <p>For serious pedestrian accident injuries — involving fractures, surgery, hospitalization, permanent disability, or significant lost wages — consult a licensed personal injury attorney. Most pedestrian accident attorneys offer free consultations and work on contingency, meaning no upfront cost.</p>

  <h2>Accuracy</h2>
  <p>We strive to keep content current. State fault rules, insurance minimums, and relevant law change periodically. Verify any information with current primary sources or a qualified attorney before relying on it for legal decisions.</p>

  <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
